<br>
I do think that if you choose the realitive safety of a zone line camp that you have to accept as part of the reward that you might get trained but then that is why you are by the zone right so you can yourself zone easily if need be?  If people camping the zone were more sure of themselves they would be deeper in most likely in a safer camp that is less likely to get trained.  Therefore they are not just innocent bystanders.  <br>
<br>
I expect anyone crossing a street to stop and look before they step out into the line of traffic.  That is why I teach my children to stop and look both ways for cars and to only proceed into the street if there are no cars coming.  Just last year I had my son run in front of a car Thank God the person driving was able to stop.  However had they not been able to stop it would have been my and my sons fault, mine for not seeing as he ran out even though I was right there and  his for not looking at all.  <br>
